Iwo Kadziela (assisted by Codex) figured out a way to generate a credible ASCII world map using 445 bytes of data:<p>The key trick is to use deflate compression, which is then wired together using this neat snippet of JavaScript. I didn't know you could use  with  URIs like this:</p><pre><code>fetch('data:;base64,1ZpLsgIxCEXnrM...==').then(
  r =&gt; r.body.pipeThrough(new DecompressionStream('deflate-raw'))
).then(
  s =&gt; new Response(s).text()
).then(
  t =&gt; b.innerHTML = '&lt;pre style=font-size:.65vw&gt;' + t
)
</code></pre>
